### API Testing Examples for UTN Campus Navigation System
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### 1. Get Complete Graph
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/graph

###

### 2. Navigate: Entrance to Library (Regular User, BFS)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 1,
  "endNodeId": 5,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "BFS"
}

###

### 3. Navigate: Ground to First Floor with Wheelchair (Must use elevator/ramp)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 3,
  "endNodeId": 17,
  "userProfile": "Wheelchair",
  "algorithm": "BFS"
}

###

### 4. Navigate: Same route with Regular user (Can use stairs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 3,
  "endNodeId": 17,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "BFS"
}

###

### 5. Navigate: Parking to Classroom (New Student - prioritizes landmarks)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 2,
  "endNodeId": 17,
  "userProfile": "NewStudent",
  "algorithm": "BFS"
}

###

### 6. Navigate: With Crutches (Penalizes stairs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 5,
  "endNodeId": 25,
  "userProfile": "Crutches",
  "algorithm": "BFS"
}

###

### 7. Navigate: Long route across buildings and floors
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 2,
  "endNodeId": 22,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "BFS"
}

###

### 8. Navigate: Same route with DFS (Compare with BFS)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 2,
  "endNodeId": 22,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "DFS"
}

###

